cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with neural machine translation. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as depthwise separable convolutions have been successful in image classification models. Additionally, it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to neural machine translation. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks for machine translation.
